"title": "4540: weeds",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4540: weeds",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Uncultivated plants or shrubs, growing wild, often among cultivated crops or plants. Jesus Christ used the image of weeds in some of his parables to illustrate sin and worldliness.</p>\n<h2>The presence of weeds indicates desolation and neglect</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:9\">ZEP 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:30-Prov24:34\">PRO 24:30–24:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:3-Isa5:6\">ISA 5:3–5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:18-Isa7:25\">ISA 7:18–7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:11-Isa32:15\">ISA 32:11–32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:8-Isa34:14\">ISA 34:8–34:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:13\">ISA 55:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:5-Hos9:6\">HOS 9:5–9:6</a></p>\n<h2>Weeds are worthless</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:23\">ISA 7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:4\">MIC 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:44\">LUK 6:44</a></p>\n<h2>Weeds were a serious problem for the farmer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:4\">HOS 10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:38-Job31:40\">JOB 31:38–31:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:24-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:24–13:30</a></p>\n<h2>Some varieties of weed were painful to the touch</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:55\">NUM 33:55</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:9-Josh23:13\">JOS 23:9–23:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:1-Judg2:3\">JDG 2:1–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:6-2Sam23:7\">2SA 23:6–23:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:3-Ezek2:6\">EZK 2:3–2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:20-Ezek28:24\">EZK 28:20–28:24</a></p>\n<h2>Weeds were destroyed by burning</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:4\">ISA 27:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:6\">EXO 22:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:18-Isa9:19\">ISA 9:18–9:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:16-Isa10:17\">ISA 10:16–10:17</a></p>\n<h2>Weeds in Jesus Christ's parables</h2>\n<p>The parable of the sower and its explanation:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:3-Matt13:8\">MAT 13:3–13:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:3-Mark4:8\">MRK 4:3–4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:5-Luke8:8\">LUK 8:5–8:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:18-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:18–13:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:13-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:13–4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:11-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:11–8:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:24-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:24–13:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:36-Matt13:43\">MAT 13:36–13:43</a></p>",
